<p>The result shows that Python 3.12 has the best performance results over Python 3.11 in the following tests: <strong>typing_runtime_protocols</strong> (<span class="ben1s">2.99x faster</span>), <strong>generators</strong> (<span class="ben1s">1.55x faster</span>), <strong>asyncio_tcp</strong> (<span class="ben1s">1.49x faster</span>). However, you may notice a drop in performance in some tests, especially in <strong>coverage</strong> (<span class="ben2s">1.69x slower</span>), <strong>unpack_sequence</strong> (<span class="ben2s">1.52x slower</span>), <strong>async_generators</strong> (<span class="ben2s">1.35x slower</span>).</p>
