<p>The result shows that Python 3.12 has the best performance results over Python 3.11 in the following tests: <strong>typing_runtime_protocols</strong> (<span class="ben1s">3.25x faster</span>), <strong>generators</strong> (<span class="ben1s">1.49x faster</span>), <strong>asyncio_tcp_ssl</strong> (<span class="ben1s">1.44x faster</span>). However, you may notice a drop in performance in some tests, especially in <strong>coverage</strong> (<span class="ben2s">1.63x slower</span>), <strong>pathlib</strong> (<span class="ben2s">1.36x slower</span>), <strong>async_generators</strong> (<span class="ben2s">1.29x slower</span>).</p>
